manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Trident Z5 RGB DDR5 Memory Trident Z5 RGB series DDR5 memory is designed for overclocked performance on compatible DDR5 platforms. Featuring a sleek and streamlined aluminum heatspreader design, the Trident Z5 RGB series is the ideal choice to build a high-performance system.

Dual-Texture Heatspreader Design Featuring a black brushed-aluminum strip inset into a metallic silver, matte black, or matte white body, and topped with a translucent RGB light bar optimized for smooth lighting, the Trident Z5 RGB is ideal for a wide variety of PC build themes.

Streamlined RGB Light Bar Designed with a streamlined light bar, the Trident Z5 RGB looks sleeker than ever. Featuring customizable RGB lighting through the G.SKILL lighting control software or supported third party motherboard software, personalizing the colors and lighting effects of the Trident Z5 RGB is a breeze.

Blazing Fast Overclocked DDR5 Performance Ushering in a new era of overclocked memory performance, the Trident Z5 RGB is engineered to high performance and quality standards. Each Trident Z5 RGB memory module is created from hand-screened DDR5 DRAM ICs to achieve high memory performance on compatible DDR5 platforms.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You're paying for quality! Don't cheap out on RAM!
reviews.reviewText: I recently invested in the G.Skill Trident Z5 RGB Series (Intel XMP) 32GB DDR5 memory, and I must say, it's worth every penny. While it may cost a bit more than its competitors, the stability, performance, and sheer aesthetic appeal make it a standout choice.First and foremost, the stability of this memory module is exceptional. It performs flawlessly, even under demanding workloads and intense gaming sessions. I experienced no crashes or performance issues, allowing me to push my system to its limits with confidence. The reliability of G.Skill's Trident Z5 series is truly impressive.Speaking of performance, this memory module is a beast. With a clock speed of 6400MHz and low CL32-39-39-102 timings, it delivers lightning-fast data transfer rates and snappy response times. This translates into improved overall system performance and a seamless multitasking experience. Whether I'm editing videos, gaming, or running resource-intensive applications, this memory keeps up effortlessly.Now, let's talk about its appearance. The matte black finish of the G.Skill Trident Z5 module is sleek and sophisticated. It adds a touch of elegance to my system and enhances the overall aesthetics. The RGB lighting is customizable, allowing me to synchronize it with other components and create stunning lighting effects that truly elevate the visual appeal of my setup.While the G.Skill Trident Z5 RGB Series may have a slightly higher price tag, the stability, exceptional performance, and stunning design make it worth every dollar. If you're looking for memory that delivers top-notch performance, impeccable stability, and looks pretty damn cool, this is the module to go for. It's a worthy investment that will enhance your computing experience and make your rig stand out from the crowd.

Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good ddr5 kit
reviews.reviewText: I had first purchased the 6600 kit. It did not go well with my asus z690-e. Had issues with bluescreen, several blue screen errors. No matter the xmp profile, I had just issues. Sure was a fault kit since I was able to boot and pass memtest86 using my brother's corsair 6600 kit. So I decided to try again but, in this case, the 6400 cl32. Installed the kits, cleared cmos, booted in bios, choose xmp2 and boom, working perfect in my system. Passed twice memtest86, no more bluescreen and the system is stable as it can be. I see a lot of people saying DDR5 is requieres fine tweek and bla bla bla. Fake. If you kit is under the memory compatibility list from MB manufacturer, it should work just fine with xmp1 or xmp2. If you are having issues like blue screen, failed memtest86 you have either fault kit or fault MB. Also always remember to have latest BIOS, firmware and chipset drivers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SK-Hynix IC's M-Die Production Month March 2023
reviews.reviewText: Just received a kit with SK-Hynix "M-Die" marked 820M and a production month of March 2023 on the module stickers. I was able to clock to 6800 Mhz on a i9-13900K with timings of CL34-45-45-108 and 1.40V. Anything higher resulted in unstable behavior and errors while running test on an ASUS Z690-E Gaming board with BIOS 2305.Ran Linpack Extreme and Cinebench test for a few hours with no issues or errors at 6800, however these modules do run a little warmer than I like around 45C+ when overclocked. At 7000+ speeds, my system would boot but memory test would fail with errors on each test run.Overall, I am extremely happy with G.Skill memory and value. I wished they made these modules with the TridentZ Royal heatsink.

I purchased this for a 7800X3d build for someone and happened by this RAM, better yet they where binned SK Hynix A-die so I could lower the RAM frequency to 6000mhz and tighten the timings.I have them configured at 6000Mhz CL28-33-33-28-68Thats CL/tRCD/tRP/tRAS/tRC in that order.You can get additional timings from looking up the Ryzen memory controller limits for the 7000 series to further tighten your timings for even more speed for work or games
Es una ram de calidad y corre a 6400 con el i9 12900k

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded my system, using this G.SKILL Trident Z5 RGB DDR5 RAM, and the performance paired with my i7-14700KF has been nothing short of exceptional. This 32GB (2x16GB) kit not only brings a substantial boost in capacity but also adds a vibrant touch to my gaming and multitasking experience.The standout feature of this Trident Z5 RAM is its compatibility with Intel XMP 3.0, ensuring seamless integration with my i7-14700KF processor. The 6400MT/s speed delivers a lightning-fast data transfer rate, providing a noticeable improvement in overall system responsiveness and application loading times.The RGB lighting on the Trident Z5 is not just eye candy; it's a showstopper. The customizable RGB lighting adds a dynamic and stylish element to my system. The synchronization options allow me to match the lighting effects with the overall aesthetics of my setup, creating a visually stunning and cohesive look.Beyond its aesthetic appeal, the Trident Z5 is a workhorse when it comes to performance. Whether I'm running resource-intensive games or handling multiple demanding applications simultaneously, this RAM maintains stability and responsiveness. The 2x16GB configuration strikes a perfect balance between capacity and speed, ensuring smooth multitasking without any lag. The timings provided on this kit make it easy and safe to overclock, providing even more performance than just out of the box! Although it wasn't bottlenecking my CPU in the first place, I always like to squeeze some extra performance out of my computer where I can.I particularly appreciate the build quality and heat dissipation capabilities of the Trident Z5. The aluminium heat spreaders not only contribute to the module's durability but also help keep temperatures in check during prolonged gaming sessions or heavy workloads.In summary, the G.SKILL Trident Z5 RGB Series DDR5 RAM has exceeded my expectations, especially when overclocking. The flawless integration, top-notch performance, and mesmerizing RGB lighting make it a standout choice for anyone looking to elevate their gaming and computing experience. If you want a RAM kit that delivers on both aesthetics and performance, the Trident Z5 is the way to go. Highly recommended!
